{"word":"πέλωρ","slug":"πέλωρ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<entryFree id=\"n80524\" key=\"pe/lwr\" type=\"main\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"entryFree\"> <orth extent=\"full\" lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"orth\">πέλωρ</orth>, <gen lang=\"greek\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gen\">τό</gen>, <sense id=\"n80524.0\" n=\"A\" level=\"1\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"sense\"> <tr_ opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"tr\">portent, prodigy, monster</tr_>, <gramGrp opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gramGrp\"> <gram type=\"dialect\" opt=\"n\" TEIform=\"gram\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Ep.\">Ep.</a></gram> </gramGrp> Noun, only nom. and acc., in early writers always of living beings, mostly in bad sense, as of the Cyclops, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">π. ἀθεμίστια εἰδώς</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:9:428\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Od.\">Od.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">9.428</biblScope> </bibl> </cit> ; <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">αὐτὴ δ᾽ αὖτε π. κακόν</foreign>, of Scylla, <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg002.perseus-grc1:12:87\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">12.87</biblScope> </bibl> ; of the serpent <bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Python\">Python</a></author>, <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ h.Ap.\">h.Ap.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">374</biblScope> </bibl> ; of a dolphin, <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">π. μέγα τε δεινόν τε</foreign> ib.<bibl default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">401</biblScope> </bibl> ; even of Hephaestus, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">π. αἴητον ἀνέστη χωλεύων</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg0012.tlg001.perseus-grc1:18:410\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ Il.\">Il.</a></author> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">18.410</biblScope> </bibl> </cit> ; later, of things, <cit TEIform=\"cit\"> <quote_ lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"quote\">εὐρυτενὴς ὠγκοῦτο π. μίτος</quote_> <bibl n=\"urn:cts:greekLit:tlg2045.tlg001.perseus-grc1:24:257\" default=\"NO\" TEIform=\"bibl\"> <author TEIform=\"author\">Nonn.</author> <title_ TEIform=\"title\"><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:LSJ D.\">D.</a></title_> <biblScope TEIform=\"biblScope\">24.257</biblScope></bibl></cit>.—Cf. <foreign lang=\"greek\" TEIform=\"foreign\">πέλωρος</foreign>.</sense> </entryFree>"}]}